9:
Don't let your guard down yet, Alk.
Shadows lurk in every corner of the
Kaleidoscope...
34:
Now to bring you home to my
professor!
40: Unhand me! You've made a mistake!
46:
Eh, the rare ones are always
oddballs. Anyway, you're coming
with me.
51: Hold it right there! Let go of him!
58:
He's not some kinda creature! Light's
my friend, and he used to be a
person—
62:
A person? Now you're just pulling my
leg.
68:
He's telling the truth! I was chosen to
fight the Lord of Shadow—
78:
Wow, you had it rough in your world.
I can relate. My professor uses his
powers to push me around all the
time.
80:
That's why I've gotta make this
delivery. If you have any complaints,
take it up with him.
86:
You can't just leave with him! That's
kidnapping!
90:
Hey, it's called doing my job as an
authorized hunter!
94:
And I've got my target drawn out
right—
101:
Uhhh, does this diagram look weird
to you guys too?
107:
S-sorry about that! Can't believe I
was looking at the thing upside
down...
111:
Name's Lyla, and I'm an
eco-research hunter.
114:
Here. Take these hunter candies as
an apology. Just one lick, and even
the fiercest monster will be brought
to heel in less than 5 minutes!
118:
So these are for monsters, and not...
us?
122:
It's totally safe for you to eat too! I
chomp them on the daily!
125:
Somehow that makes me trust
them even less...
127:
Anyway, why were you looking for
that creature?
129:
It was a request from the Guild!
Which technically went to my
professor, but uh... He sent me.
130:
Apparently, the Kaleidoscope's been
affecting the local ecology. They
needed some researchers to look
into it.
134:
It must be because the
Kaleidoscope is a link between
worlds.
137:
You know about that? Hunh. Must
not be your run-of-the-mill
adventurer then.
139:
Say, you haven't seen this weird
creature around, have you?
144: You mistook me for this BEAST?
149:
Wait. It looks like one of those things
from Endless Blue...
153:
So you HAVE seen it? Where?! Tell
me, tell me! I really need to grab one!
155:
I don't have much time before my
professor decides to roast me alive!
159:
Uh... Doesn't sound like this guy
should be a professor.
162:
Some academics are just devils in
disguise, I swear. Anyway, info
please?
166:
How consequential is this quest of
yours?
170:
VERY! The fate of the world depends
on it! No way I can walk away
empty-handed!
174:
I'm starting to think you need to find
a new job...
182:
Well, there's been rumors of a sea
monster rising from the depths. Not
sure if it's what you're looking for, but
it's the only lead we've got. Light, you
don't mind showing her the
you-know-what Flipper, right?
185:
Not at all. Lyla, we shall help you
save this world.
192: Let's hash out a plan then!
